    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. Meticulously maintained with a full Viton vacuum line refresh and documented high-compression rotor faces, the powertrain remains in peak factory specification. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis retains its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and lightweight forged components, ensuring the legendary 50/50 weight distribution is preserved. Finished in flawless factory paint with a pristine interior, this specimen exhibits zero chassis flex or UV degradation. A turn-key, collector-grade vehicle for the discerning rotary enthusiast.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
